The UniParc identifier (UPI) is the unique identifier assigned to a distinct protein sequence in [UniParc](https://www.uniprot.org/uniparc). It consists of the characters “UPI” followed by 10 hexadecimal characters (0–9, A–F). A UPI is stable across [releases](https://www.uniprot.org/help/synchronization), and can therefore be used to cite a protein sequence in UniParc.
Example:[UPI000005156C](https://www.uniprot.org/uniparc/UPI000005156C/entry)

A UPI is never removed, changed, or reassigned to a different sequence.
